Top-Ranked India Defeats West Indies by 63 Runs in Cricket Series Opener

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-06-24T00:43:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/top-ranked-india-defeats-west-indies-by-63-runs-in-cricket-series-opener.html
Top-ranked  India  beat West Indies by
63 runs to go 1-0 up in their three-match Test cricket series.  Praveen Kumar and Ishant Sharma each took three wickets as
India dismissed the home team for 262 in its second innings on
day four at Sabina Park in Kingston,  Jamaica , after setting a
victory target of 326.  India recovered from 85-6 on the opening day to post its
fifth win in 43 Tests in the Caribbean with a day to spare.
Rahul Dravid was named man of the match after top scoring with
112 in Indiaâ€™s second-innings 252.  The second Test starts June 28 in Barbados and the final
match begins July 6 in Dominica.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
